.TH "ssam_try_set_controller" 9 "ssam_try_set_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_try_set_controller \- Try to set the main controller reference.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_try_set_controller
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller to which the reference should point.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the main controller reference to the given pointer if the reference
hasn't been set already.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns zero on success or -EEXIST if the reference has already
been set.
